# Unit 2 - Task 05

## Aim

Demonstrate how to pull a Docker image, tag it, push it to Docker Hub, install software inside a running container, verify the installation, and save the changes using Docker commit.

## Step 1: Pull Alpine Linux Image

docker pull alpine:latest

## Step 2: Tag the Image

docker tag alpine:latest dishatribedy/alpine-php:v1

## Step 3: Login to Docker Hub

docker login

## Step 4: Push Image to Docker Hub

docker push dishatribedy/alpine-php:v1

## Step 5: Run Container Interactively

docker run -it alpine:latest sh

## Step 6: Update Package Index

apk update

## Step 7: Install PHP

apk add php

## Step 8: Verify PHP Installation

php -v

## Step 9: Exit Container

exit

## Step 10: Commit Container Changes

docker commit <container-id> dishatribedy/alpine-php:v2

## Result

The Alpine image was pulled, tagged, and pushed to Docker Hub. PHP was installed inside the container and verified successfully. The container changes were saved as a new Docker image using docker commit.

